annotationA: LD10456p; It is involved in the biological process described with: ribosome biogenesis; regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase I promoter
annotationB: Probable DNA-directed RNA polymerases I and III subunit RPAC2; DNA-dependent RNA polymerase catalyzes the transcription of DNA into RNA using the four ribonucleoside triphosphates as substrates. Common core component of RNA polymerases I and III which synthesize ribosomal RNA precursors and small RNAs, such as 5S rRNA and tRNAs, respectively (By similarity); Belongs to the archaeal RpoL/eukaryotic RPB11/RPC19 RNA polymerase subunit family
